-- Meteor Hires David Stuff for Listed Structured Product Business
-- B y   A l a s t a i r   M a r s h
-- 2012-06-12T11:04:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/meteor-hires-david-stuff-for-listed-structured-product-business.html
Meteor Asset Management Ltd., the
London-based structured note provider, hired David Stuff as a
managing director to oversee the firm’s distribution of
exchange-listed products.  Stuff will expand Meteor’s sales of structured securities
traded on the  London  Stock Exchange to clients including
investment advisers, wealth managers and private banks, Kriss
Mulcahy, a product development executive at Meteor in London,
said in an e-mail.  Stuff joins from  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc  where he
was a director of U.K. sales for investor products and equity
derivatives. Prior to RBS, he worked at  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM)  and
Barclays Plc.  Structured notes are securities that package debt with
derivatives to offer customized bets to investors. Derivatives
are contracts whose value is derived from stocks, bonds,
currencies and commodities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alastair Marsh in London at 
